      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NAUGHTY NORM (7) was an impressive winner last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 2 lengths (22.87) at Mt Gambier. Looks well placed and can measure up again. PAW SAUNDRA (1) was out of character last run when missing the frame, finishing sixth (22.81) in a Free For All at this track. Normally fast to begin but shuffled back last time. Has a good record here at this journey. Was a winner at her only start from this draw. Better than last start and can bounce back. ASTON FUMIKO (2) goes very well here starting seven times for three wins and two minors. Was out of placings last time (22.35) at Ballarat in a Grade 4/5, finishing fifth and beaten 2.5 lengths. Can hit the frame with the right run. HENRIKSEN (5) has top-three aspirations after placing last time.",
